   I am an educator and want information on Senator Bingaman and the
   Senate for my classes, or want to know what he is doing that affects my
   field.

   The following sections will be of interest to you:

   My Biography
   If you class is doing a Model Senate, my biography will provide
   information for them on my personal history, my work history, and my
   goals as Senator. Go there now
   My photo
   Click here to download a copy of my photo for your class. Go there now

   Committee Assignments
   In order to effectively pursue my legislative initiatives, it is
   important that I be on committees that have jurisdiction over the
   issues I deal with.  This list shows the committees I am on and
   provides links to their homepages. Go there now
   Student's Page
   Your students may be interested in pursing this section of my homepage
   for information on how the Senate works and other insights into the
   operations of the Congress.  Although the information has been divided
   into sections for different grade levels, students may find interesting
   material outside their level as well.  Go there now

   Education Issues
   This section discusses my legislative initiatives in education. Go
   there now

   Learning About the Senate
   The Senate web server has an excellent section for those interested in
   learning about the Senate. Go there now
   Historical Documents
   The Library of Congress has the full text and other information
   available about the Declaration of Independence, the Constitution, the
   Federalist Papers, and even some early Congressional documents. Go
   there now
